.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATE.DAYOFYEAR" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDate.dayOfYear \- Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.dayOfYear
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]dayOfYear\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] instances returns a positive integer
representing the 1\-based day index in the year of this date.
The first day of this year is \f[CR]1\f[R], and the last day is the
\f[CR]daysInYear\f[R].
It is calendar\-dependent.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]dayOfYear\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
To create a new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object with the desired
new \f[CR]dayOfYear\f[R] value, use the \f[CR]add()\f[R] or
\f[CR]subtract()\f[R] method with the appropriate number of
\f[CR]days\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using dayOfYear
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq);
console.log(date.dayOfYear); \f[I]// 182\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01[u\-ca=chinese]\(dq);
console.log(date2.dayOfYear); \f[I]// 140\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date3 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2020\-07\-01\(dq);
console.log(date3.dayOfYear); \f[I]// 183; 2020 is a leap year\f[R]
.EE
.SS Changing dayOfYear
\f[CR]PlainDate\f[R] does not support changing \f[CR]dayOfYear\f[R]
directly.
To change the day of the year, you need to first figure out the
difference in days to your desired day of the year, then use
\f[CR]add\f[R] or \f[CR]subtract\f[R] to adjust the date accordingly.
For example, to change to the 100th day of this year (whether before or
after):
.IP
.EX
\f[B]function\f[R] getDayInSameYear(date, destDayOfYear) {
  \f[B]return\f[R] date.add({ days: destDayOfYear \- date.dayOfYear });
}

console.log(
  getDayInSameYear(Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq), 100).toString(),
); \f[I]// 2021\-04\-10\f[R]
console.log(
  getDayInSameYear(Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-01\-01\(dq), 100).toString(),
); \f[I]// 2021\-04\-10\f[R]
console.log(
  getDayInSameYear(Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2020\-01\-01\(dq), 100).toString(),
); \f[I]// 2020\-04\-09\f[R]
.EE
.PP
By default, \f[CR]with()\f[R] constrains the day to the range of valid
values.
So you can always use \f[CR]{ month: 1, day: 1 }\f[R] to set the day to
the first day of the year, even if the first day does not have the
number \f[CR]1\f[R].
Similarly, the following will set the day to the last day of the year,
regardless of how many days are in the last month or year:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] lastDay = date.with({ month: Number.MAX_VALUE, day: Number.MAX_VALUE }); \f[I]// 2021\-12\-31\f[R]
.EE
